/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/judgments/chain-01.md:5:The attacker is mostly right. The original chain is disciplined and worth keeping, but only as a narrowly scoped obstruction branch, not as a broad discovery program for the mission's beyond-De-Giorgi mechanism. Its main strengths are real: it asks for estimate-level gains, it front-loads killing cosmetic rewrites, and it is willing to end negatively. Its main weaknesses are also real: it leaves the target architecture under-specified, states the Tao screen too loosely, treats geometry too much as contamination, and makes the negative endpoint easier to earn than the positive one.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/judgments/chain-01.md:23:This is a central flaw. "Not obviously preserved by Tao's averaged model" is too loose. The refined chain needs a concrete statement of what exact NS feature is supposed to fail in the averaged setting and where that failure enters the localized estimate.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/judgments/chain-01.md:71:### 8. Step 3 treats geometry too late and too cleanly separable from algebra
